cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CR

The paper deals with computer vision techniques for identifying the photographer behind a photograph. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves feature extraction and classification, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also discusses the security implications of identifying the authorship of a photograph, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
